description.narrative:
UNICEF with the Ministry of Health and Child Care, National AIDS Council and implementing partners engaged and empowered adolescents and young people living with HIV, including pregnant and breastfeeding girls to increase demand for SRH/HIV services in supported districts including during Cyclone Idai, cholera response and post-recovery, resulting in 100% of Young Mentor Mothers actively supporting 740 pregnant and breastfeeding girls and young women living with HIV in 5 districts and 180 out of a target of 120 peer supporters actively supporting children, adolescents and young people living with HIV to access services in the 7 selected districts.
